That directory is mounted into your sandbox so you can read source files
directly — `ls {{.Worktree}}`, `cat`, etc. Use it to inform your task
breakdown. Do NOT try to `git clone` from GitHub or `gh auth login`: the
sandbox has no network credentials and those calls will fail. Treat the
worktree as read-only for planning; the task agents that run later get their
own write access in the same worktree.
